div.p:
I. He performs Duties to God from a a right Principle: And this is twofold;


1. A principle of Faith. And,

2. A principle of Love.

(2) From the reason of the caution observe further; 
                  Obser. 2 That the confideration of the all-seeing eye of God, who sees and takes notice of your behaviour in your addresses to him, should incite and provoke you to take heed of the manner how you do hear the word of God. The allseeing Eye of God should be a motive to

restrain us from the least secret sin: as Job saies, I made a covenant with my eyes, why then should I think upon a maid? for doth not the Lord see all my waies, and count all my steps?
